#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.181"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.181:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: yodhājīvavaggo (s1-3) | yodhajīvavagga (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.181:0.2"
msgid "19. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "19. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.181:0.3"
msgid "181. Yodhājīvasutta "
msgstr "181. A Warrior "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.171, sc1
msgctxt "an4.181:1.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato yodhājīvo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a warrior with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship. "

msgctxt "an4.181:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.181:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo ṭhānakusalo ca hoti, dūrepātī ca, akkhaṇavedhī ca, mahato ca kāyassa padāletā. "
msgstr "He’s skilled in the basics, a long-distance shooter, a marksman, one who shatters large objects. "

msgctxt "an4.181:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato yodhājīvo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "A warrior with these four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.181:1.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.181:1.6"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.181:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ṭhānakusalo ca hoti, dūrepātī ca, akkhaṇavedhī ca, mahato ca kāyassa padāletā. "
msgstr "He’s skilled in the basics, a long-distance shooter, a marksman, one who shatters large objects. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.181:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ṭhānakusalo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant skilled in the basics? "

msgctxt "an4.181:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

msgctxt "an4.181:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ṭhānakusalo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is skilled in the basics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.181:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dūrepātī hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant a long-distance shooter? "

msgctxt "an4.181:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: *all* form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "an4.181:3.3"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā … "
msgstr "They truly see any kind of feeling … "

msgctxt "an4.181:3.4"
msgid "yā kāci saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "an4.181:3.5"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "an4.181:3.6"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near, *all* consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "an4.181:3.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dūrepātī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is a long-distance shooter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.181:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhaṇavedhī hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant a marksman? "

msgctxt "an4.181:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "It’s when they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "an4.181:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhaṇavedhī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is a marksman. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.181:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahato kāyassa padāletā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant shatter large objects? "

msgctxt "an4.181:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahantaṃ avijjākkhandhaṃ padāletā. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant shatters the great mass of ignorance. "

msgctxt "an4.181:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahato kāyassa padāletā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant shatters large objects. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.181:5.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.181:5.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

